<paragraph id="8B8C0E0CFF98FFA68790703BFD3E044E" blockId="24.[178,1085,552,630]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">
V e r b r e i t u n g (nach 3, 3): 
<collectingCountry id="F3244E9CFF98FFA68568703BFD000466" box="[586,676,586,606]" name="Austria" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">Österreich</collectingCountry>
(Linz, 
<collectingRegion id="49F7C0EEFF98FFA685D3703BFC9B0466" box="[753,831,586,606]" country="Austria" name="Salzburg" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">Salzburg</collectingRegion>
) (LIN, SWA, ZSM). Alle bekannten Exemplare wurden aus Wirten gezogen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3295D87FF98FFA6879070F7FC0F04CB" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8C0E0CFF98FFA6879070F7FC0F04CB" blockId="24.[178,1085,645,755]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">
L e b e n s w e i s e Wirt: 
<taxonomicName id="4C33758FFF98FFA686F870F7FC9604A3" authority="(FABRICIUS)" baseAuthorityName="FABRICIUS" box="[474,818,645,667]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Perizoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis id="B947D21EFF98FFA686F870F7FD0A04A3" box="[474,686,646,667]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">Perizoma sagittatum</emphasis>
(FABRICIUS)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C33758FFF98FFA6846070F4FC6C04A3" baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[834,968,645,667]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geometridae</taxonomicName>
) (2 Serien; 
<collectingCountry id="F3244E9CFF98FFA6879070D3FEB90480" box="[178,285,674,696]" name="Austria" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">Österreich</collectingCountry>
) (LIN, SWA, ZSM). Der Wirt ist univoltin; seine Raupen leben von August bis September an Blüten und Samen von 
<emphasis id="B947D21EFF98FFA6857470B1FD6204ED" box="[598,710,704,725]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1319">Thalictrum</emphasis>
. Die gezogenen Parasiten tragen nur die Angabe, dass sie Ende Mai beziehungsweise Mitte Juli geschlüpft sind.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
